726640f-a.title: Queens: 111th Street - 50th Avenue
726640f-a.text:
Flushing Meadwww Park (ueens): Shown, under construction,
are the Corona gates of the New York World's Fair, 1939-40, on
the east side of 111th Street between 50th and 53rd Avenues.
View 1 is south on 111th Street; note the two steel
prows of the Marine Industry Buiiing.
May 30, 1938
Views 1,2

726683f-a.title: Queens: 111th Street - 50th Avenue
726683f-a.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Tueens): One of the gates to the
grounds of the World's Fair 1939-40, on the east side of 111th
Street at, 5Oth Avenue. The Fair's theme--the Trylon and Peri-
sphere--appears on the right; in view 2 appear the Railroads
Building (left), pert of the general Motors Building (right),
and World's Fair buses of the Fifth Avenue Coach Company.
June 23, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
